# eval_kaggle.jsonl — held-out Kaggle RVT/IFC eval bench
# EVAL ONLY — NOT USED FOR TRAINING. See data/kaggle-eval-bench/PROVENANCE.md.
#
# Schema per row:
#   id            string   sha256[:12] of (source_url + filename)
#   prompt        string   derived natural-language prompt for the LoRA
#   gold_elements object   {IfcWall: N, IfcSlab: N, ...} element-type counts
#   gold_path     string   relative path under data/kaggle-eval-bench/
#   schema        string   "IFC2x3" | "IFC4"
#
# Rows are populated after running:
#   kaggle datasets download artemboiko/rvtifc-projects -p data/kaggle-eval-bench/ --unzip
#   python scripts/select-kaggle-subset.py
#
# This file is intentionally empty until the download + selection step runs.
# eval-kaggle-bench.py handles an empty JSONL gracefully (zero rows, exit 0).
